radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is dilated to 1.3 cm, fluid filled, and hyperemic. A rounded calcified structure with a central lucency is present at the tip of the appendix. The visualized heart is normal. The lung bases are clear. The liver is unremarkable without focal or diffuse abnormality. The gallbladder, intra- and extra-hepatic bile ducts, pancreas, spleen, bilateral adrenal glands, and bilateral kidneys are normal. The small and large bowel are normal in course and caliber. The bladder and terminal ureters are normal. The prostate is unremarkable.
